	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.57]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some folks say all into STA to maximize HP during the high end game.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you go on raids (or plan to a lot) then maybe that is a good idea.  If you plan to solo mostly then kiting does not require as many HP.  But STA is the hardest stat to raise with gear.<br><br>DEX is important since it helps prevent 'missed notes' - the bard equivelent of a spell fizzle.<br><br>CHA is needed to help with charming and mezzing targets. It also reduces the chance a target will aggro on you after a failed lull.<br><br>STR is good since bards do wear plate armor.  It can get heavy.  As a bard you are not a primary melee class. Your job is not based soley on how much weapon damage you do.<br><br>AC is nice since bard songs draw aggro to the bard much like heal spells draw aggro to a cleric/druid/shaman.  <br><br>In my case I put the most points into DEX and CHA with a touch into STR.  I started out with FS plate armor and now use RyGor.  Its been quite adequate.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
