<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=104610113456460></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104610113456460><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104610113456460>RE: Downtime</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104610113456460#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>706 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 24th 11:11 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards don't regen mana like anyone else (meditate caps at 1).  So, if you are high enough to use mana based charm (and do use the mana based charm) you will see a lot of downtime for mana regen.  However, all but a couple of bard songs don't ever use mana.  So, the downtime issue becomes HP regen.  Bards can do that very quickly with mana-less songs.  Necro's generally have to cast mana-using life tap spells.  Bard's don't have to sit to regen HP fast. They can do it while on the move.<br><br>Since bards have really poor meditate skills it is common for higher level bards to get Flowing Thought items as soon as they can.  Those work standing or sitting.  Bard's cannot use their own songs to regenerate their own mana, BTW.  The song only works on others. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
