	   <a name=104617957464148></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104617957464148><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104617957464148>RE: Downtime</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104617957464148#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>706 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 25th 8:58 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends on what song the bard is playing:<br><br>Hymn of Restoration for example, only regens HP. How much HP/tick depends on the level of the bard and the quality of the instrument being played. Sitting only adds one more HP per tick to the overall rate. Which is why I almost never sit. Why, when I can regen on the run?&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards are about mobility.<br><br>There is another song (level 34) that does HP and 5 mana per tick.  Although the mana is constant the HP/tick is based on level of the bard and the quality of the instrument.<br><br>Other songs, similar but more potent, are gained a 41, 47, and 55.<br><br>Dark Pact Increases mana by 2/tick at a cost of 4 HP/tick. Even Hymn of Restoration on my 29 bard with a Combine Mandolin does 11 HP per tick.  It cost no mana to play the song.  My bard has 750 HP total. How does that compare to the mana of a 29 Necro?<br><br>One other note:  Last night I was using my bard to Fear Kite in South Karana.  Angstlich's Appalling Screech (Fear song) costs no mana. Twisted that with Selo's Consonant Chain (snare/slow song - no mana) and Denon's Disruptive Discord (AoE 30HP/tick DOT - no mana). I took down 2 aviak rooks and 3 Tesch Mal Gnolls (dk blue cons) and lost about one full bubble of HP in the processes.  I didn't use a single weapon; just my Torin's Horn (easy for a level 25-30 to farm). I use Ry'Gor armor and Netherbian chitin (just so you know he is not twinked to the gills).  I did take them one at a time and not as a single group.  So what does that tell you about my downtime? I didn't have much. 60 secs of regen song and I was 100%. <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 25 08:33:38 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
