	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can do it but i dont recommend it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stuns and missed notes (bard equivelent of fizzles) make these macros very awkward.  Anyway, if you really must you use the /stopsong command to stop one song and the /cast # (where # is the number of the spell gem slot for the song you want to play.<br><br>/stopsong<br>/cast 1<br>/stopsong<br>/cast2<br>/stopsong<br>/cast 3<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
