	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.54]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes. Bards have a line of songs in the Lull, Mezz, and Charm lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Whether or not the bard gets aggro on the Lull songs depends on the bards CHA.  The higher the CHA the less chance a failed lull song will generate aggro.  The first Lull song is gained at level 8.<br><br>Bards can mezz starting at level 15. But the level 15 song has a restriction to mobs under level 31.  At level 28 the bard gets the upgrade.  Duration is only 18 seconds on either song.<br><br>Bards can charm for up to 18 sec at level 27 but that only works on mobs under level 38. There is an upgrade later, though.  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
