	   <tr><td colspan=2>What is your song line up for twisting?<br><br>My Vah Shir bard is level 28.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most of the time the groups I join are cleric/shaman heavy (lucky me!) and tank/chanter light.  So for my twist line up I have:<br><br>Anthem de Arms (or if I am only melee I use JWW)<br>Selo's Consonant Chain (used for pulling in addition to its other benefits)<br>Psalm of Warmth (for the DS)<br><br>I keep Pixie Strike mem'd for CC even if we have a chanter. Last night we had no chanter and I kept 3 mobs mezzed and did nothing else for the whole fight.  But our group had 2 tanks, a wizard and a shaman so no problem there.<br><br>Otherwise I have SA, Sonorus Clouding, HoR, and one swap slot.  I rarely use Charm. Even with my CHA at 103 I have a bad time with it. Probably just me needing practice.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
