	   <a name=104315914860007></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104315914860007><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104315914860007>RE: Haste</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104315914860007#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>706 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 21st 9:54 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>From what I have read on the enchanter boards the hard haste cap is about 105%.&nbsp;&nbsp;That total can be from one item and one spell.  There is a bard song that can stack with the spell and item haste and will go over the haste cap.  That is the level 60 Warsong, I think. Otherwise, if multiple spells, songs and items are involved the haste calculation takes the highest %'s and adds those.<br><br>I am not sure if the effects of the LoH and SoD stack.  It maybe the higher of the two which is the LoH. The Sash is 24% I have read.  Experiment and see for yourself.<br><br>As for what songs you should sing - I am not an authority at that high a level for bards.  However, every bard post-60 I have talked to (my mentor is 65) has said that song selection is conditional.  Are you grouped or solo? Are you fighting caster or melee mobs?  Are you kiting or meleeing? If kiting, what kind/style of kiting?  So, the answer to you question really varies based on the conditions.<br><br>I read a thread yesterday on a tank board where they pretty much agreed that in the high end game tanks find AC buff songs useless. They are mostly at or near the hard cap anyway by then. They want resists, HP, and haste songs that break the cap.<br><br>Between items and the group enchanters they are already at the cap so the song has to put them over.  Otherwise its a waste of a twist.  Even regen spells and songs, though helpful are not nearly as useful as a CHeal.  The damage the tanks take comes in too fast. Damage shields are very popular with tanks. Especially, if they stack. So, at level 57 Rondo's would be a great group song.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
