	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104294337329009><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104294337329009>RE: New bard advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104294337329009#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85584><span id=Scholar>barfly</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>99 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jan 18th 9:57 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.63]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My advice would be to do a little vendor farming in PoK and see if you can come up with any of the tradeskill components that PCs are using (razorfiend talons, sandstorm pearls, putrid ooze).&nbsp;&nbsp;Give those to your bard and park him/her in the bazaar -- if your server has a good supply of high-level tradesmen, you will have lots of cash in no time.<br><br>I started a Half-elf week ago, spent the first 4 levels in Qeynos and amassed 30pp on my own from newbie drops.  Went to PoK and bought some items that were within my budget (and I knew were in demand), sold in bazaar for good plat, and repeated (example: putrid ooze costs 6pp from merchants, and sells for 300pp+ in bazaar).<br><br>Make about 2K per day with minimal time in bazaar -- have regular people who buy the stuff. My bard bought some good HP items (coterie general cape, spider fur belt, fire wedding rings), some nice, fast weapons that weren't too expensive (crystalline short sword, sainy's claw, smoldering brand), and during my time in the bazaar selling, I watched for good deals on other armor pieces and managed to fill most of my slots with either Teir'dal (good for STR, DEX and INT)or Koada'dal armor (good for STR, DEX, and CHA).<br><br>You may also get lucky while vendor mining -- found a Hero Bracer for 13pp and Shield of the Seneschal for 22pp (kept bracer, sold shield for 2k).  Also found a Tambourine of Ritual for 5gp.<br><br>When I got bored, I went and hunted for pelts and silks -- selling leather padding is also profitable. <br><br>I have only reached level 10, but I have everything I need/want now, and I will not have to worry about armor until level 50.  This is easy to do, as I have followed the exact same method with seven other characters on 2 different servers -- doesn't really even require any help from main characters if you are dilligent and patient.  Just depends on how much you enjoy shopping (I don't have two computers/accounts or this would be alot easier).<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Jan 18 22:19:38 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
