	   <tr><td colspan=2>Get Ry'Gor armor or Fine Steel Plate.<br><br>Newbie Vah Shir bards dont get armor quests specifically for bards like the other races. However, there are some decent newbie, non-class specific, armor quests in Shar Val and Shadeweaver's Thicket you can do.<br><br>For weapons you can get some fairly decent stuff cheap.&nbsp;&nbsp;Try vendor mining.  I got my primary weapon, Ice Tooth Claws, for 12pp off a vendor. The phosphorecent fiber I use off hand I got from my 48 rogue as a hand me down.<br><br>By farming pelts and spiderling silks as a newbie I was able to get enough together for a guildmate to make me some Fine Steel armor. She did the combines. I either farmed or bought the materials.  I got a full set for about 200pp. The farming was no problem since I was low enough to still get experience for killing the mobs.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
