	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fill in your armor slots with Ry'Gor. You will be good until you can get Singing Steel.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you can find the bard Twilight Sea armor for sale its worth buying.  Questing for it yourself is a pain and by the time you get all the components you have already outgrown it.<br><br>Alternate BP I would consider is Treeweave AC 25 STR +10.  About 600pp nowadays on my server. Frankly, the Neth Chitin will last you a good long time - into your upper 30's I would think.<br><br>Spend your money on Velium Fire Wedding Rings, Crested Spaulders AC 11 STA 9(?), Platinum Star Ruby Veil.  Get your DEX over 100 and your CHA over 110 and you will be fine.  I am told that more CHA unless you get over 150 is no help.  You won't really need CHA until level 27 anyway.<br><br>STR is important so you can carry armor. STA is important for HP and fatigue. Get both over 100 to start.  You may or may not drop the sheild when you get dual wield at level 17.  Its up to you and honestly, its circumstantial.  If you are not meleeing in a group the extra AC from a shield is helpful.  Sometimes I don't melee at all- like when I fill in for enchanter or healer roles.  Then the shield is good when I draw aggro.<br><br>The stats I would emphasize buying gear, in order of preference, are AC, HP, STR, DEX, CHA, STA, Mana, and INT (our mana at higher levels is INT based). We don't need mana until upper 40's.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
