	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104208093720493><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104208093720493>RE: DA</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=104208093720493#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=200639><span id= >Ronney</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 8th 10:22 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Does a wizzie have Double Attack either? When it comes down to it, bards are not a high DPS melee class; they get their damage through other methods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their lacking DA doesnt necessarilly mean that they cannot deliver large amounts of damage.  Let me give an example.  <br><br>Hill Giants in Rathe are killable by druids from about 30 (they need C3 and will die occasionally).  Bards *can* also kill HG at this level (chant kiting as HG would generally be too high to charm reliably at this level), and have no downtime (as no mana useage) but it would take a long time to kill your giant. Druid does this better.<br><br>But take the same bard at 50 with a decent drum and a bit of skill and (if he can find them) he can take 4 giants at a time (charm 1, get it to take agro of 2 others, and chant the 4th ... then break charm and chant the first that is by now nearly dead).  And still no downtime.  Your druid is left medding for ages after attempting 4 at once, and will probably take longer killing them anyway.  And WAR/MNK/SK/ROG (ie the other non-healing melee hi-DPS classes) would be able to solo 2 (not at the same time) at the very most wihtout requiring lengthy downtime to heal.<br><br>Put it this way ... <br><br>A solo bard should have no downtime unlike other classes as they dont *need* mana to solo and there is no reason why (beyond lvl 26 and AE fear) they ought to get hit so much as to need extensive healtime.<br><br>A bard grouped with melee classes may do less DPS with his weapons, but he will make up for this by eg. hasting the party / slowing the mob / adding a DS ... and all at the same time.  And with a pure caster group (viable after 20) hes pumping the casters with mana for less downtime.  And of course almost all a bard sings stacks with effects given by other classes.<br><br>One word of caution .. do not choose a bard if you dont like being kept forever busy by groups :) <br><br>Ronney &lt;Nexus of Dreams&gt;<br>Antonius Bayle<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan  8 22:06:49 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
